Tips for Renting a Car in Albania
1. Book in Advance

Especially during peak tourist seasons (summer), availability can be limited.

2. Inspect the Car

Check for any existing damage before driving off.

3. Understand Insurance

Make sure you know what’s covered and what’s not.

4. Ask About Mileage Limits

Some rentals include daily mileage caps (e.g., 250 km/day).

5. Confirm Cross-Border Policies

If you plan to visit neighboring countries, ask for permission in advance.

